/Tp: Wave Peak Period  or Peak period = Wave period associated with the largest peak in the power spectrum (seconds)
/Tp_sea: Peak Sea Wave Period associated with the largest peak in the sea region of the power spectrum. (seconds)
/Dp_sea: Peak Sea Wave Direction - peak sea direction at the peak period in the sea region relative to true north reference (degrees)
/Hsig_sea: Significant Wave Height in the sea region of the power spectrum. (meters)
/Tp_swell: Peak Swell Wave Period associated with the largest peak in the swell region of the power spectrum. (seconds)
/Dp_swell: Peak Swell Wave Direction associated with the largest peak in the swell region of the power spectrum. true north reference (degrees)
/Hsig_swell: Significant Wave Height in the swell region of the power spectrum. (meters)
/Hmax: Maximum Wave Height or Height of Largest Wave from Zero Crossing Analysis (meters)
/Tmax: Maximum Wave Height or Period of Largest Wave from Zero Crossing Analysis (seconds)
/YEAR MONTH DAY HOUR MINUTE SECOND = Date/Time Data Acquisition (UTC)
